If an order is charged but Cashback redemption fails for various reasons (Order status: charged), we must get error details from NCR.

The error will only appear for customers who have this particular club and/or have such errors in the system (Cashback Charge Failed) - Loyalty members are eligible to redeem cashback.

{color:#4c9aff}*Strategy testing:*{color} We cheat fake data to test local, and after release on production: we will go back to double-check this feature to see if it shows the corresponding error by real data

{color:#ff5630}*Backoffice - CRM > Order List page:*{color}

# Check the Alerts dropdown with the new option: “Cashback Charged Issues” -  בעיות חיוב קאשבק (/) 
# Check the display for Cashback Charged issues that will allow filtering and searching for one of the five possible errors (/) 
- Insufficient Reward Points Balance: לא מספיק יתרת נקודות תגמול (/) 
- Bug - Reward Points Balance Mismatch: באג - אי התאמה של יתרת נקודות תגמול (/) 
- Communication Failure: כשל בתקשורת (/) 
- Reward Points Expired: פג תוקף נקודות התגמול (/) 
- Other: אחר
# Check the Cashback charged issues dropdown when clicking on option(s) → It should show text on this field (/) 
# Check the Cashback charged issues dropdown when clicking on “Remove Selection” : מחק בחירה → It should clear this field to empty (/) 
# Check the Cashback charged issues when selecting more than 2 options → It should have results related to the errors. (/){color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Verify the resulting filter when selecting the “Cashback charged issues” and selecting one of five options → The table result shows the order with the error same as the option chosen or NOT result (/){color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Verify the resulting filter when selecting “Cashback charged issues” and *don’t choose* error options → The table result shows the orders with both error or NOT result (/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Verify the error details tooltip will appear when hovering over the error icon on the "Payment Method" column with the error details of the order cashback charge failed.  (/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Verify the resulting filter when selecting the other fields (Order status, other numbers, POS other id, etc…) and Cashback Charged Issues → The table result shows the orders correctly with the data filter.(/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Verify that the errors are shown in both English and Hebrew .(/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Make an order with an insufficient reward points balance for Cashback redemption → verify the error: *Insufficient Reward Points Balance* on the Orders page in the Backoffice(/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Make an order with a system error is causing incorrect points balance to display on the website, even when there are not enough points for redemption → verify the error: *Bug - Reward Points Balance Mismatch* on the Orders page in the Backoffice (/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Make an order with Communication failure with the MultiPass server or communication issues at the branch level → verify the error: *Communication Failure* on the Orders page in the Backoffice(/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Make an order with Points expired due to removal after 180 days from the accumulation date, even if the order was placed before points expired → verify the error: *Reward Points Expired* on the Orders page in the Backoffice(/) {color:#36b37e} *passed with fake data*{color}
# Make an order: there is another error from NCR that we don’t recognize → verify the error: *Other* on the Orders page in the Backoffice (i){color:#0747a6}*need to be data*{color}

